    "reasoning": "The problem involves two parts. First, we determine the probability that during the removal of balls from a jar with 8 red and 2 blue balls, there exists a time when blue balls exceed red balls. Using combinatorial analysis and the reflection principle, we find the number of violating paths (where blue > red at some point) is 10 out of 45 total paths. This simplifies to a probability of 2/9, with gcd(2,9)=1. Thus, n = 1 + 2004 = 2005.\n\nFor the second part, we analyze the subdivision of an L-shape. Each subdivision of an L-shape produces 4 smaller L-shapes. Due to rotational symmetry, each L-shape (regardless of orientation) contributes exactly one L-shape in the original orientation when subdivided. Therefore, after n subdivisions, the number of L-shapes in the original orientation is 4^(n-1). For n=2005, this is 4^2004.",
